00:31:54,080 --> 00:31:57,120
I'm rehearsing alone but I’m still failing.

586
00:31:57,840 --> 00:32:00,000
If I have to do this in front of everyone,

587
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:00,320
If I have to do this in front of everyone,

588
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:04,000
I’ll crash and burn right from the start.

589
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:07,280
It’s okay, Hill. You can do it.

590
00:32:08,920 --> 00:32:10,120
Really, Yuka?

591
00:32:11,920 --> 00:32:12,920
Okay, I’ll try again.

592
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:14,720
I’ll practice some more, Yuka.

593
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:15,440
Okay.

594
00:32:15,760 --> 00:32:17,680
I hope you have a wonderful night.

595
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:30,480
Super cool,

596
00:32:31,040 --> 00:32:32,280
super dangerous.

597
00:32:36,160 --> 00:32:37,720
I already failed at holding hands.

598
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:39,280
Now the speech too?

599
00:32:39,760 --> 00:32:42,400
This is way harder than I thought!

600
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:48,160
Boss.

601
00:32:51,600 --> 00:32:54,160
You sure talk about me a lot.

602
00:32:56,200 --> 00:32:57,000
I know.

603
00:33:02,360 --> 00:33:03,360
First of all,

604
00:33:03,520 --> 00:33:04,960
before you speak,

605
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:08,600
you stand up straight and be confident.

606
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:12,880
Yes, sir.

607
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:16,640
Otherwise, you won’t be able to say a word.

608
00:33:17,720 --> 00:33:18,440
Got it?

609
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:23,280
Got it.

610
00:33:42,800 --> 00:33:43,600
Okay.

611
00:33:44,520 --> 00:33:45,320
All done here.

612
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:47,680
That's not good enough.

613
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:48,120
What?

614
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:50,280
Glass noodle salad is almost gone.

615
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:53,320
Oh! I’ll go grab it.

616
00:33:53,320 --> 00:33:54,000
In a flash.

617
00:33:54,120 --> 00:33:56,040
We'd be fine if you'd brought it earlier.

618
00:33:56,040 --> 00:33:57,800
And the guests won't have to wait.

619
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:00,000
I'm fine. We’re all friends here.

620
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:01,000
I'm fine. We’re all friends here.

621
00:34:01,720 --> 00:34:02,640
I eat what's left.

622
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:03,600
No, Pao.

623
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:05,000
If you can't handle this,

624
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:06,280
good luck with the rest.

625
00:34:06,760 --> 00:34:07,880
Apologize to the guest.

626
00:34:08,800 --> 00:34:09,600
What?

627
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:11,560
Apologize.

628
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:13,600
I…

629
00:34:15,080 --> 00:34:15,880
I’m sorry.

630
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:16,600
Hey, hey.

631
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:18,200
Don't be so serious.

632
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,600
I like grilled pork neck.

633
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:20,400
No.

634
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:21,960
Go get glass noodle salad, now.

635
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:23,720
Right now?

636
00:34:27,520 --> 00:34:28,320
Yes.

637
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:29,560
Sir Yes Sir!

638
00:34:29,720 --> 00:34:30,720
I'm on it.

639
00:34:32,360 --> 00:34:33,080
Good.

640
00:34:33,160 --> 00:34:33,840
Hey, hey.

641
00:34:34,360 --> 00:34:36,200
Hurry up and don’t slack off!

642
00:34:37,200 --> 00:34:38,000
Careful!

643
00:34:38,360 --> 00:34:38,800
There.

644
00:34:38,800 --> 00:34:39,200
Easy.

645
00:34:42,200 --> 00:34:43,080
You're leaving?

646
00:34:43,080 --> 00:34:44,000
Well,

647
00:34:44,160 --> 00:34:44,640
Well I—

648
00:34:44,760 --> 00:34:46,800
I just…

649
00:34:46,800 --> 00:34:47,600
I'm full!

650
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:49,560
You know? The food goes down the stomach

651
00:34:49,560 --> 00:34:51,440
and send a signal straight to the brain

652
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:52,440
that I'm full. So bye.

653
00:34:52,440 --> 00:34:53,240
Just kidding.

654
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:55,960
I just wanted to test his patience.

655
00:34:56,160 --> 00:34:57,640
You should’ve played along!

656
00:34:57,920 --> 00:34:58,600
Testing?

657
00:34:58,600 --> 00:34:59,200
Exactly.

658
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:00,000
Jeez, you should've told me.

659
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:00,800
Jeez, you should've told me.

660
00:35:00,800 --> 00:35:01,800
Would've be so fun!

661
00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:02,360
Alright.

662
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:03,960
I'm in. Let's mess with him.

663
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:04,800
Be convincing.

664
00:35:04,880 --> 00:35:05,520
That's easy.

665
00:35:05,560 --> 00:35:06,040
Good.

666
00:35:06,040 --> 00:35:06,960
Give him hell.

667
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:08,400
Here’s glass noodle salad.

668
00:35:08,800 --> 00:35:09,720
Good.

669
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:10,720
Here you go!

670
00:35:11,160 --> 00:35:12,280
That's great.

671
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:12,960
However,

672
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:14,280
I’d like some soft soda.

673
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:15,600
Please?

674
00:35:16,600 --> 00:35:17,200
Oh…

675
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:18,200
Sure!

676
00:35:18,560 --> 00:35:19,200
So

677
00:35:19,760 --> 00:35:20,920
two bottles.

678
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:21,720
Sounds good?

679
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:23,400
Sounds good to me.

680
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:26,360
Mind opening them for me too?

681
00:35:26,400 --> 00:35:26,920
Please?

682
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:28,680
That won't be a problem, sir.

683
00:35:29,120 --> 00:35:29,920
Be right back!

684
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:30,800
Got it?

685
00:35:30,880 --> 00:35:31,520
Yes, sir.

686
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:31,920
Go on.

687
00:35:31,960 --> 00:35:32,320
Yes!

688
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:38,600
It’s rare to see him work this well!

689
00:35:39,200 --> 00:35:39,800
How was it?

690
00:35:39,800 --> 00:35:40,480
Terrific.

691
00:35:42,920 --> 00:35:44,800
Freshly made glass noodle salad!

692
00:35:48,040 --> 00:35:48,800
And…

693
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:51,520
What am I supposed to do?

694
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:59,000
Listen to your feelings.

695
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:02,280
Inside, here.

696
00:36:05,720 --> 00:36:08,240
Then let them form into words.

697
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:09,600
Speak from the heart.

698
00:36:11,960 --> 00:36:15,280
Just like when you spoke to me

699
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:19,400
about wanting to keep Yuka's game going.

700
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:40,680
I'm ready now, Boss.

701
00:36:46,720 --> 00:36:47,680
Did you know?

702
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:52,520
On my first day of work,

703
00:36:54,760 --> 00:36:57,560
out of nowhere, someone came

704
00:36:58,200 --> 00:36:59,600
and crushed my dreams.

705
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:05,920
That person was my own boss.

706
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:08,640
Let's wrap up "Yuka! Love Me Please"

707
00:37:08,640 --> 00:37:09,920
properly.

708
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,440
Junior Game Designer

709
00:37:11,440 --> 00:37:12,360
No, you can't.

710
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:17,200
And then…

711
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:19,720
That same person

712
00:37:20,960 --> 00:37:22,800
gave me the opportunity

713
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:27,160
to learn that if we want to succeed

714
00:37:28,200 --> 00:37:30,120
we have to put in effort.

715
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:33,400
Hello.

716
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:36,480
Please come this way.

717
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:43,000
Over the past three months

718
00:37:43,880 --> 00:37:45,160
I admit

719
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:49,800
that working here has been exhausting.

720
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:54,000
Sometimes I felt hopeless.

721
00:37:55,120 --> 00:37:58,280
Thought I wasn’t cut out for this job.

722
00:38:03,280 --> 00:38:05,040
But you showed me

723
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:08,680
that even you kept fighting.

724
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:14,320
I want to see everyone succeed and be happy

725
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:16,680
doing the work we love.

726
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:22,840
I want us to be a team
that walks hand in hand

727
00:38:23,720 --> 00:38:26,680
and succeeds together.

728
00:38:30,280 --> 00:38:31,600
Others get discouraged too.

729
00:38:32,600 --> 00:38:34,160
It's not just me.

730
00:38:37,880 --> 00:38:41,160
There’s one thing Boss once said to me.

731
00:38:44,520 --> 00:38:46,040
"Together. Leave no one behind."

732
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:51,920
So today,

733
00:38:53,960 --> 00:38:55,440
I want to tell you

734
00:38:57,520 --> 00:38:58,400
that I…

735
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:00,000
I’m not going to leave you behind.

736
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,680
I’m not going to leave you behind.

737
00:39:07,160 --> 00:39:08,400
Please keep your promise.

738
00:39:09,320 --> 00:39:10,800
Don’t leave us, Boss.

739
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:22,400
Please don’t fire me, Boss.

740
00:39:27,480 --> 00:39:28,520
Finally,

741
00:39:29,080 --> 00:39:31,400
I want to thank

742
00:39:31,520 --> 00:39:32,480
fate,

743
00:39:33,520 --> 00:39:37,080
for guiding me to all of you.

744
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:40,360
I don’t have many friends.

745
00:39:41,040 --> 00:39:41,880
But here,

746
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:45,640
I’ve come to realize

747
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:47,680
that beyond just being a good team

748
00:39:49,560 --> 00:39:51,600
we’re also good friends.

749
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:59,720
Let’s face the challenge
of our strict boss together!

750
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:05,960
Woohoo!

751
00:40:08,240 --> 00:40:10,480
[cheering]

752
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:11,320
That's great!

753
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:14,040
[cheering]

754
00:40:14,040 --> 00:40:16,280
Woohoo!

755
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:58,720
Very cutesy!

756
00:41:58,800 --> 00:41:59,800
Yeah!

757
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:02,480
Pao. This brings back memories.

758
00:42:02,480 --> 00:42:04,600
Back when "Yuka! Love Me Please"

759
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:06,160
still had its spark.

760
00:42:07,200 --> 00:42:07,840
Oh yeah.

761
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:10,120
This might be the very first time

762
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:12,080
that Yuka came into the real world.

763
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:13,360
Amazing!

764
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:14,240
[cheering]

765
00:42:14,240 --> 00:42:14,920
Awesome!

766
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:19,560
Honestly, I feel a little embarrassed

767
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:20,880
doing something like this.

768
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:31,320
Hill.

769
00:42:31,800 --> 00:42:34,600
If it weren't for him,
I wouldn’t have done it.

770
00:42:35,120 --> 00:42:36,880
It was his idea.

771
00:42:40,200 --> 00:42:41,000
Wow.

772
00:42:41,720 --> 00:42:42,520
His idea?

773
00:42:44,720 --> 00:42:45,760
Thank you, Boss.

774
00:42:46,360 --> 00:42:47,200
Arigatou (Thanks)!

775
00:42:50,880 --> 00:42:52,600
This is probably the first time

776
00:42:52,600 --> 00:42:54,800
he’s gone this far for a new employee.

777
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:57,080
She's right.

778
00:42:57,080 --> 00:42:57,800
That's right.

779
00:42:58,000 --> 00:42:59,800
Hmm, interesting.

780
00:43:01,080 --> 00:43:04,440
Now that Hill has shared his feelings,

781
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:06,200
it’s your turn, Boss.

782
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:08,000
Got anything you’d like to say

783
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:09,560
to the newbie here?

784
00:43:10,360 --> 00:43:11,960
Come on, just say it!

785
00:43:13,080 --> 00:43:13,800
Go on, Boss.

786
00:43:13,800 --> 00:43:14,360
Say it!

787
00:43:14,360 --> 00:43:14,920
Yeah!

788
00:43:15,000 --> 00:43:15,600
Boss!

789
00:43:15,600 --> 00:43:16,520
[cheering]

790
00:43:16,520 --> 00:43:17,200
Woohoo!

791
00:43:19,480 --> 00:43:20,200
Well…

792
00:43:24,160 --> 00:43:24,960
From now on,

793
00:43:27,800 --> 00:43:29,000
work hard, okay?

794
00:43:32,360 --> 00:43:33,000
That’s it?

795
00:43:35,680 --> 00:43:36,360
Alright!

796
00:43:37,800 --> 00:43:38,640
Yay!

797
00:43:41,760 --> 00:43:43,360
Boss is ruthless!

798
00:43:52,720 --> 00:43:53,680
Food is ready!

799
00:43:53,680 --> 00:43:54,320
Great.

800
00:43:54,320 --> 00:43:54,880
Thank you.

801
00:43:56,480 --> 00:43:57,400
Enjoy the meal.

802
00:43:57,880 --> 00:43:59,200
Wait up, man.

803
00:44:00,200 --> 00:44:01,280
You're pretty for a guy.

804
00:44:01,280 --> 00:44:02,200
What’s your name?

805
00:44:03,280 --> 00:44:04,160
It's Phat.

806
00:44:05,080 --> 00:44:07,080
Would you like any more drinks?

807
00:44:07,080 --> 00:44:08,120
I'll go get them.

808
00:44:08,600 --> 00:44:09,680
I want to take you out.

809
00:44:09,840 --> 00:44:11,000
For two nights.

810
00:44:12,960 --> 00:44:15,200
I think you are too drunk.

811
00:44:15,400 --> 00:44:16,760
Let me get you water.

812
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:17,920
Alright?

813
00:44:23,160 --> 00:44:24,120
Bring it on.

814
00:44:24,560 --> 00:44:25,480
How about this?

815
00:44:26,280 --> 00:44:28,280
If I pay you to keep me company,

816
00:44:28,920 --> 00:44:29,760
will you do it?

817
00:44:31,400 --> 00:44:33,000
I think I should get back to work.

818
00:44:33,360 --> 00:44:34,000
Don't.

819
00:44:34,400 --> 00:44:36,000
I’ll pay you well.

820
00:44:36,480 --> 00:44:37,760
Just come with me.

821
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:42,200
Have some respect.

822
00:44:43,160 --> 00:44:44,280
A grown man like you

823
00:44:44,800 --> 00:44:46,400
should know when to stop.

824
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:48,720
You're drunk. Go home and rest, Aof.

825
00:44:49,080 --> 00:44:51,200
Wow, you're wearing matching shirts!

826
00:44:51,640 --> 00:44:53,040
If I'd known you were his guy,

827
00:44:53,040 --> 00:44:54,280
I'd have left you alone.

828
00:44:56,080 --> 00:44:57,400
Well, I’ll be on my way then.

829
00:44:58,160 --> 00:44:58,800
Let’s go.

830
00:44:59,320 --> 00:45:00,000
Not so fast.

831
00:45:01,680 --> 00:45:02,880
Apologize to him first.

832
00:45:06,000 --> 00:45:07,000
Sorry, man.

833
00:45:07,400 --> 00:45:08,800
Guess I drank too much.

834
00:45:09,000 --> 00:45:10,320
I really should go home.

835
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:13,040
Sorry, Bay.

836
00:45:13,040 --> 00:45:14,200
Don’t be mad, alright?

837
00:45:15,320 --> 00:45:16,120
Fair enough.

838
00:45:39,200 --> 00:45:40,400
Hey, Hill.

839
00:45:42,280 --> 00:45:43,200
There you are.

840
00:45:44,280 --> 00:45:45,200
I looked all over.

841
00:45:45,760 --> 00:45:47,120
Where have you been?

842
00:45:49,280 --> 00:45:51,400
Just around here, actually.

843
00:45:56,600 --> 00:45:57,520
Ms. Jeans.

844
00:45:58,000 --> 00:45:58,680
Yeah?

845
00:45:58,680 --> 00:45:59,640
I…

846
00:46:00,320 --> 00:46:03,760
I have something to confess.

847
00:46:03,760 --> 00:46:05,000
I feel like

848
00:46:06,400 --> 00:46:07,360
I have to say it.

849
00:46:09,080 --> 00:46:09,880
Confess?

850
00:46:14,280 --> 00:46:14,760
Yes.

851
00:46:14,760 --> 00:46:15,440
I…

852
00:46:15,440 --> 00:46:21,080
Just now, I thanked everyone.

853
00:46:21,800 --> 00:46:24,800
But I didn’t get to thank you, Ms. Jeans.

854
00:46:26,360 --> 00:46:27,000
I…

855
00:46:28,680 --> 00:46:30,320
I want to thank you, Ms. Jeans.

856
00:46:30,880 --> 00:46:31,680
For…

857
00:46:33,000 --> 00:46:34,680
Being the reference for Yuka-chan.

858
00:46:35,360 --> 00:46:36,600
I really feel that

859
00:46:36,960 --> 00:46:39,080
without someone like you as a reference,

860
00:46:40,160 --> 00:46:42,360
game like "Yuka! Love Me Please"

861
00:46:42,360 --> 00:46:43,720
would’ve never existed.

862
00:46:45,600 --> 00:46:46,400
Thank you.

863
00:46:49,800 --> 00:46:52,600
You seem really sentimental.

864
00:46:55,560 --> 00:46:56,360
Indeed.

865
00:46:58,160 --> 00:47:00,000
Yuka had helped me

866
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:01,000
Yuka had helped me

867
00:47:01,840 --> 00:47:03,600
through a lot of tough times.

868
00:47:04,960 --> 00:47:05,760
I never thought

869
00:47:09,600 --> 00:47:11,240
that one day I’d be here.

870
00:47:11,760 --> 00:47:15,360
Working at this company

871
00:47:15,960 --> 00:47:16,400
and

872
00:47:17,520 --> 00:47:20,400
standing in the office that created Yuka-chan.

873
00:47:21,080 --> 00:47:24,840
Even though I wasn’t part of the project,

874
00:47:25,680 --> 00:47:29,680
just being here makes me incredibly proud.

875
00:47:32,200 --> 00:47:33,000
Don’t forget.

876
00:47:34,160 --> 00:47:36,600
You’re a part of Yuka-chan too.

877
00:47:37,800 --> 00:47:39,760
You help keeping the game alive.

878
00:47:42,800 --> 00:47:43,280
